('item-0209',209,'Space','A · Hook','Space — gate passage','gate','article','','400-460L','Unit-gate UNSEEN passage. UNSEEN topic (NOT taught in L1-L4): ''Comets: Icy Visitors'' — a 445L informational passage (~230 words) explaining what a comet is (a ball of ice and dust that orbits the Sun), why a comet grows a glowing tail when it comes close to the Sun (cause/effect), the time-order of a comet''s visit (far away -> nears the Sun -> tail forms -> swings away), with a labeled diagram of a comet (nucleus, tail) and an arrow showing its orbit path. Dominant structures present so the gate can probe all assigned standards: main-idea+details, cause/effect, sequence, comparison (comet vs. planet), a diagram for RI.3.7, sentence-to-sentence connections for RI.3.8, and Tier-2/affix vocabulary (icy, glowing, frozen, distant, returning) for L.3.4. Must be a topic NOT read in the lessons.'),
